  AndroidManifest.xml for the safemode_library AAR.

  An AAR manifest declares permissions, metadata, and min SDK.
  It does NOT declare an Application class or Activities — those live
  in the app that consumes this library.

  android:minSdkVersion 33 = Android 13 (AAOS Tiramisu) — the minimum
  version where the VHAL AIDL V3 interface we depend on is available.
-->
<manifest xmlns:android="http://schemas.android.com/apk/res/android"
    package="com.myoem.safemode">

    <!--
      QUERY_ALL_PACKAGES is NOT needed — we use a direct ServiceManager lookup,
      not an Intent/PackageManager query.

      If the app targets SDK 31+, Android enforces package visibility filtering.
      Because we access via ServiceManager (hidden API) rather than Intent, no
      <queries> declaration is needed in the app's manifest either.
    -->

</manifest>
